<HEADLINE>
10 STUDENTS OF NTU'S ENGLISH MBA PROGRAM WIN SCHOLARSHIPS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 9 (CNA) 05/09/07  20:49:09 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Ten students attending the English-language Master of Business
Administration (MBA) program at National Taiwan University's
College of Management each received a scholarship worth
NT$100,000 (US$6,000) Wednesday from the Fubon Group through the
Fubon Cultural and Educational Foundation.
</P>
<P>
Hung Mao-Wei, dean of the NTU's College of Management, and Victor
Kung, president of Fubon Financial Holding Co., jointly presided
over a ceremony to award the Fubon-NTU English MBA Elite
Scholarships for 2007.
</P>
<P>
The 10 recipients of the scholarships are: Chuang Chi-hsuan, Yang
Chien-chou, Su Yu-li, Hsieh Ai-chen, Chen Li-min, Yu Ai-hsin, Li
Yuan-hao, Chang Wei-chen, Lien Teh-hsin and Huang Chih-chen.
</P>
<P>
According to a screening committee for the scholarships, the
winners -- all first-year students -- were selected on the basis
of academic performance, classroom participation and discussion,
English language proficiency, educational background and previous
employment experience.
</P>
<P>
In addition to presenting these students with scholarships, the
Fubon Group has indicated that it will provide opportunities for
them to work in Fubon's affiliated business organizations as
interns during the summer vacation.
</P>
<P>
National Taiwan University's College of Management and the Fubon
Group jointly established the English-language MBA program in
2004, with a view to creating an all-English learning environment
for selected graduate students and cultivating talented
individuals who can adapt to world trends for the benefit of
Taiwan's enterprises, according to Fubon's executives.
</P>
